cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as 3D facial structure estimation, facial key-point detection, and image transformation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which suggests the possibility of using machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves geometric transformations, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Lastly, the paper involves the use of adversarial image translation techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
